{"TopicId":181413,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Vessel Switching and docking","CreatedByName":"tawpik","CreatedById":194759,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-15T15:09:36Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"tawpik","CreatedById":194759,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-15T15:09:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there anyway to Switch between close parked Vehicles and rendezvous Vehicles(Without using mod)?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen i tried its not possible by clicking the vessels, and the map is completely covered by one vessel icon.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nit would be great if i can switch vessels just on the third person view.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be great if there is a feature that can control both vessels at the same time for docking.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbesides if i have a small vessel docking port magnets are too strong, is there a way to adjust magnets strength or disable it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ni\u0027d love to know if there is a solution for that\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-15T21:02:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022[\u0022 and \u0022]\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RealKerbal3x","CreatedById":183830,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-15T21:08:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/194759-tawpik/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022194759\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/194759-tawpik/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@tawpik\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor controlling 2 vessels at the same time for docking, you kind of can. Switch to your target vessel and target your main vessel, then use the \u2018point to target\u2019 \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E mode. Then switch back to your main vessel and click the same \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E mode. The ships will automatically align - this\u00A0way you can make your docking approach without having to worry about manually aligning with the docking port. However, if you\u2019re docking with a space station and the port is off-axis, you should click on the port and set it as your target.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs for adjusting the magnetism on docking ports, unfortunately it\u2019s not in the stock game. However Editor Extensions Redux has it as well as a ton of other useful stuff.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5311544183\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/127378-151-editor-extensions-redux-released-with-selectroot-merge-stripsymmetry-nooffsetlimits/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:247px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHope that helped!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(I was about to inform you about the bracket key thing but \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/32993-razark/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002232993\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/32993-razark/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@razark\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0ninja\u2019d me \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-01-15T21:09:33Z\u0022 title=\u002201/15/2019 09:09  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 15, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by RealKerbal3x\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003ERemoved whitespace\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-15T21:15:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you want the ability to switch vessels in flight by clicking on them (Which is really, really handy if you have more than two ships close together that are interacting), you want this guy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed7954317871\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/141180-16-easy-vessel-switch-evs-v110/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:228px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAt the very least they need to implement the ability to ignore debris while using [ and ] in stock.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tawpik","CreatedById":194759,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-16T00:13:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223522862\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181413\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221547586175\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002232993\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022razark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, razark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022[\u0022 and \u0022]\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey Thanks, Didnt know for years ...\u00A0 i could have saved so much time. I get back to tracking station every time i switch before ....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Snark","CreatedById":125662,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-16T00:46:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223522974\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181413\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221547597586\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022194759\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tawpik\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n34 minutes ago, tawpik said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHey Thanks, Didnt know for years ...\u00A0 i could have saved so much time. I get back to tracking station every time i switch before ....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHeh, yeah, that one\u0027s super useful.\u00A0 \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0 You\u0027re not the first person to be late finding it, either-- it\u0027s not super discoverable.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNote that it only works for craft that are within 2.3 km of each other.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut even if you get farther apart than that, you still don\u0027t have to go all the way back to the \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cu\u003Etracking station\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/em\u003E... just go to the map view, click on the other ship\u0027s icon, and choose the \u0022switch to\u0022 option.\u00A0 Saves a couple of steps over going all the way back to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022;)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022;)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-16T01:00:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223522974\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181413\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221547597586\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022194759\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tawpik\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n44 minutes ago, tawpik said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDidnt know for years ...\u00A0 i could have saved so much time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, it\u0027s much easier than switching to map view or tracking station to switch.\u00A0 It also lets you switch to/between Kerbals on EVA.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223522991\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022181413\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221547599619\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022125662\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Snark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, Snark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027re not the first person to be late finding it, either-- it\u0027s not super discoverable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee, that\u0027s what happens when you don\u0027t read the manual that comes with the game... \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_rolleyes.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:rolleyes:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI miss the days when games came with books.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}